## Chapter 14 The Supporting Roles

- qualitative, some of our research is generative, which is understanding the problems we need to solve, and some of our research is evaluative, which is assessing how well our solutions solve the problem.
- User Researcher they can help find the right type of users, craft the right types of tests, and learn the most from each user or customer interaction.
- Data Analysts help teams collect the right sort of analytics, manage data privacy constraints, analyze the data, plan live-data tests, and understand and interept the results.
- Test Automation Engineers - write automated tests for your product. Partially replaced the QA colleagues. In many teams engineers and QA people work side by side to write code and tests, with some members focusing on areas where they have more skill. 
